{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents antitoxin PezA, found mainly in lactobacillales. PezA is the antitoxin component of a type II toxin-antitoxin (TA) system in which PezT is the cognate toxin. In this system, PezA functions as a transcriptional repressor with PezT as a corepressor. PezT interacts with PezA and forms a tight complex [[cite:PUB00056183], [cite:PUB00048622]].</p>\n\n<p>PezAT TA system is a PezA2PezT2 heterotetramer, which has a dumbbell-shaped arrangement with an internal 2-fold symmetry [[cite:PUB00048622]]. The PezAT core is formed by a stack of two PezA antitoxin polypeptide chains that are sandwiched between two PezT toxin molecules whose dyad axis lies parallel to the PezA homodimer interface ([pdbe:2P5T]).</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR035569", "name" "Antitoxin epsilon/PezA domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"NF041575" "type II toxin-antitoxin system antitoxin PezA"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Antitoxin PezA", "short" "PezA"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 1, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 19, "taxa" 175, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 264, "sets" 0, "proteins" 264, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 219}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR048181", :literature {"PUB00056183" {"URL" nil, "issue" "3", "authors" ["Mutschler H" "Gebhardt M" "Shoeman RL" "Meinhart A."], "ISO_journal" "PLoS Biol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.1001033", "medline_journal" "PLoS Biol", "title" "A novel mechanism of programmed cell death in bacteria by toxin-antitoxin systems corrupts peptidoglycan synthesis.", "year" 2011, "raw_pages" "e1001033", "volume" "9", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 21445328}, "PUB00048622" {"URL" nil, "issue" "27", 